  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Best Large Desk Pad for Work 2026</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated June 2026 · Evaluated 7+ models</div>

      <nav class="toc" aria-label="Table of contents">
        <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</a></li>
          <li><a href="#ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</a></li>
          <li><a href="#quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-overall">Best Overall</a></li>
          <li><a href="#best-budget">Best Budget</a></li>
          <li><a href="#buying-guide">Buying Guide</a></li>
          <li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <p>A large desk pad does two jobs at once: it protects your desk surface from scratches, spills, and wrist friction, and it creates a unified visual base that makes a cluttered setup look intentional. The problem is that most pads fail at one of those jobs — they look good but stain permanently the first time you spill coffee, or they are waterproof but the mouse sensor will not track on them. We evaluated seven large pads based on their specifications and material properties to find which ones actually deliver on both.</p>

      <h2 id="how-we-evaluated">How We Evaluated</h2>
      <p>We evaluated 7 large desk pad models based on product documentation, specifications, feature analysis, and pricing comparison. Our evaluation methodology follows the <a href="/how-we-test/">ToolStep review protocol</a>, analyzing product documentation, specifications, features, and pricing. Each product was assessed across identical criteria to ensure fair comparison.</p>
      <p>We evaluated each product on four criteria: Performance (30%), Build Quality (25%), Value (20%), and Ease of Use (25%). Scores were compiled from specification analysis and feature evaluation, not marketing claims. For mouse tracking, we assessed sensor compatibility based on material specifications and surface treatment descriptions. For spill resistance, we evaluated material properties based on manufacturer documentation of waterproofing and stain resistance features, including liquid beading behavior and cleanability claims.</p>

      <h2 id="ranking-methodology">Ranking Methodology</h2>
      <p>Our rankings are based on weighted scoring across four dimensions:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Performance (30%)</strong> — Mouse tracking accuracy and surface consistency</li>
        <li><strong>Build Quality (25%)</strong> — Edge stitching, material durability, and waterproofing</li>
        <li><strong>Value (20%)</strong> — Price-to-performance ratio compared to alternatives</li>
        <li><strong>Ease of Use (25%)</strong> — Cleaning, flatness out of the box, and wrist comfort</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="quick-comparison">Quick Comparison</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
